Spanish Banks Renegotiated $14 Billion of Loans, Expansion Says

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-05-12T06:30:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/spanish-banks-renegotiated-14-billion-of-loans-expansion-says.html
Spanish banks renegotiated loans
worth 10 billion euros ($14 billion) last year in a bid to limit
defaults, Expansion reported.   Banco Santander SA and its Banco Espanol de Credito SA unit
refinanced 2.3 billion euros of past-due loans, the newspaper
said, citing information from the lenders.    Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
